# Cron Builder

[![PyPI](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/cron-builder.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/cron-builder/)
[![Python Version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/cron-builder.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/cron-builder/)
[![License](https://img.shields.io/pypi/l/cron-builder.svg)](https://github.com/yourusername/cron-builder/blob/main/LICENSE)

A fluent, type-safe Python library for building and validating cron expressions with an intuitive API.

For full documentation, see the [README](README.md).

## Quick Example

```python
from cron_builder import CronBuilder, Weekday

# Every day at 9:30 AM
cron = CronBuilder().at(9, 30)
print(cron)  # 30 9 * * *

# Weekdays at 2:30 PM
cron = CronBuilder().at(14, 30).on_weekdays()
print(cron)  # 30 14 * * 1-5
```
